<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880120-0189 </DOCNO><HL> Switzerland's Trade Gap Grows </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EUROP </CO><IN> MON </IN><DATELINE> BERN, Switzerland  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Swiss trade deficit widened in December and in all of 1987, the Federal Office of Industry, Trade and Labor said.    In December alone, the deficit, which isn't seasonally adjusted, grew to 447.2 million Swiss francs ($326.2 million) from 118.8 million francs in November. Imports rose 3.4%, to 6.60 billion francs ($4.81 billion), while exports fell 1.8%, to 6.15 billion francs.    In the full year, the deficit widened to 7.69 billion francs from 6.50 billion francs in 1986. Imports increased 2.3%, to 75.17 billion francs, while exports rose 0.7%, to 67.47 billion francs. </TEXT></DOC>